{
  "texts": [
    "The Cyberspace Administration of China (CAC) implemented pioneering rules on \"deep synthesis\" technology that took effect in January 2023 -one of the world's first comprehensive laws targeting deepfakes.",
    "These regulations prohibit the use of deepfake or other generative AI technology to produce and disseminate \"fake news\" or content that could disrupt economic or social order.",
    "Service providers offering generative AI tools are required to authenticate users' real identities and to ensure their algorithms do not generate prohibited content.",
    "Critically, the rules mandate that any AI-generated or AI-manipulated content must be clearly labeled as such, both through visible markers in the content (e.g., watermarks or disclaimers) and through embedded metadata (China Daily, 2025).",
    "This dual labeling requirement is intended to ensure public awareness that a piece of media is synthetic and to facilitate traceability via hidden \"fingerprints\" in case the content is reposted or altered."
  ]
}